manifest.name: dotnet-deps-parser
manifest.description: Generate a dep tree given a collection of manifests

scripts.test: npm run lint && npm run unit-test
scripts.unit-test: npm run build && tap test/lib -Rspec --timeout=300 --node-path ts-node --test-file-pattern '/\.test\.[tj]s$/'

manifest.readme:
![Snyk logo](https://snyk.io/style/asset/logo/snyk-print.svg)

***

[![Known Vulnerabilities](https://snyk.io/test/github/snyk/dotnet-deps-parser/badge.svg)](https://snyk.io/test/github/snyk/dotnet-deps-parser)


Snyk helps you find, fix and monitor for known vulnerabilities in your dependencies, both on an ad hoc basis and as part of your CI (Build) system.

## Snyk .Net Dependencies Parser
Given a `.net` and `.net core` manifest and project files builds a dep tree

## Supported Manifest Files

* `packages.config`
* `project.json`
* `project.assets.json`
* `.csproj`
* `.vbproj`
* `.fsproj`
